---
description: Do not skip or gate tests to hide failures; surface real CI signal.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Tests — no hiding failures

- Do not add `t.Skip`, commented-out test bodies, or `if testing.Short()` branches to make suites green while scenarios are broken or unimplemented.
- Prefer fixing the code or the test harness; if a test is genuinely optional or prohibitively slow, split it with an explicit build tag or documented `-short` policy agreed in the repo — do not invent silent skips while iterating.
